Day2
----
1) convert ts to js
    -> tsc -w
2) to generate the tsconfig.ts
    -> tsc -init (will genereate the tsconfig.json)
2) install express server
    -> npm install i express
3) start the server
    -> create a file server.js
    -> node server.js

    angular install
    -------------=
    npm i -g @angular/cli

    version
    ------
    ng v
    hello world prg
    ----------------
    1) ng new step1-helloworld

    2) navigate to step1-helloworld

    3) ng serve -> start the server

    flow
    ----
    everthing have to configured in angular.json
        -> index.html,source folder can be changed here
        asserts -> to put all the images required for the project
        styles -> css can be applied here
        scripts -> js can be applied here
        aot -> 
        prefix -> app.component we can use this prefix or every where we can use this prefix in the project
    index.html -> main.ts -> AppModule ->

    create a new component
    ----------------------
    1) create a new component in app folder (city.component.ts)
    will have selector : 'app-citi',
    template:'<h1>Hello from city component</h1>'
    2) add this component in app.module.ts
        ->declarations and bootstrap
    3) add it in index.html <app-citi></app-citi>

    4) for tag attribute we have use [] and function in tag ()

ng g application step1binding

ng serve --project <project name> --> to run the specfic project in an application

<input [(ngModel)]="title" type="text">
to use above ngModel we need to import FormModel in app.Module.ts file

to create a component
ng g c komali --project=step1binding --flat -t -s -skiptests=true
